clinical_study.brief_title: Study Comparing the Efficacy of Two Ibuprofen Formulations
clinical_study.official_title: A Study Comparing the Efficacy of Two Ibuprofen Formulations

lead_sponsor.agency: Wyeth is now a wholly owned subsidiary of Pfizer

clinical_study.source: Wyeth is now a wholly owned subsidiary of Pfizer

brief_summary.textblock: This is a study of healthy volunteers to compare how quickly different ibuprofen products relieve dental pain.

primary_outcome.description: Subjects evaluated the time to "First Perceptible" Relief by depressing a stopwatch at the moment they first began to experience "perceptible" relief and the time to "Meaningful" Relief by depressing a second stopwatch at the moment they first began to experience "meaningful" relief. These times were recorded up to 6 hrs after dosing. Range: up to 6 hrs, a lower number is better.

secondary_outcome.measure: Pain Intensity Difference (PID) Scores at Each Individual Time Points
secondary_outcome.description: PID is based on the 4-point categorical pain severity score ranging from 0 (none) to 3 (severe), this value was derived by subtracting the score at each post-dosing time point from the baseline score, so that a higher positive value is indicative of greater improvement.

secondary_outcome.measure: Pain Relief (PR) Scores at Individual Time Points
secondary_outcome.description: Response to the question "How much pain do you have from your starting pain?" was recorded on a 5-point categorical pain relief scale (None (0), A Little (1), Some (2), A Lot (3) or Complete (4)) at designated time points after study medication was taken.

secondary_outcome.measure: Time-weighted Sum of Pain Relief + Pain Intensity Difference (SPRID) From 0-2 Hours and 0-6 Hours
secondary_outcome.description: SPRID is a derived endpoint from the pain relief and pain intensity difference scores from 0-2 hours and 0-6 hours. PRID=PID+Pain Relief Score. SPRID-02 range: -2 (worst) to 14 (best); SPRID 06 range: -6 (worst) to 42 (best).

secondary_outcome.measure: Pain Relief Combined With Pain Intensity Difference (PRID) Scores at Individual Time Points
secondary_outcome.description: PRID (PRID=PID+PR) is a derived endpoint from the pain relief and pain intensity difference scores at each time point. Range: -1 (worst) to 7 (best).

secondary_outcome.measure: Time-weighted Sum of Pain Intensity Difference (SPID) From 0-2 Hours and 0-6 Hours
secondary_outcome.description: SPID is a derived endpoint from the pain intensity difference scores from 0-2 hours and 0-6 hours. Range: -2 (worst) to 6 (best); -6 (worst) to 18 (best).

secondary_outcome.measure: Time-weighted Sum of Pain Relief Scores (TOTPAR) From 0-2 Hours and 0-6 Hours
secondary_outcome.description: TOTPAR is a derived endpoint from the pain relief scores from 0-2 hours and 0-6 hours. Range: 0 (worst) - 8 (best); 0 (worst) - 24 (best)
The elapsed time from dosing until the patient indicated first perceptible relief, provided the subject also indicated achieving meaningful relief.

intervention.description: 2 placebo gels capsules delivered as a single dose.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion criteria :
- Outpatients with post-operative pain following surgical extraction of third molars,
- examined by the attending dentist or physician and medically cleared to participate in the study,
- in general good health and have no contraindications to the study or rescue medication.
Exclusions criteria:
- any serious medical condition,
- acute localized dental infection at the time of surgery ,
- females who are pregnant, lactating, of child-bearing potential, or post-menopausal for less than 2 years and not using a medically approved method of contraception.

participant_flow.recruitment_details: Patients were recruited in the United States from August 2008 to October 2008.
participant_flow.pre_assignment_details: During the screening period, the Investigator or his/her designee examined each subject and completed a checklist of the inclusion/exclusion criteria in order to determine the patient’s eligibility. Surgery occurred within 14 days of the screening visit.

outcome.title: Time to Meaningful Pain Relief
outcome.description: Subjects evaluated the time to “First Perceptible” Relief by depressing a stopwatch at the moment they first began to experience “perceptible” relief and the time to “Meaningful” Relief by depressing a second stopwatch at the moment they first began to experience “meaningful” relief. These times were recorded up to 6 hrs after dosing. Range: up to 6 hrs, a lower number is better.
outcome.population: All randomized patients who were dosed with study product, indicated a baseline score of at least 2 out of 4 on the Categorical Pain Severity Rating Scale and confirmed a pain assessment of at least 50 mm out of 100 mm on the Visual Analog Scale (VAS). Median pain relief was not reached for the placebo participants within 360 minutes.
